before.enText: of a university degree, a rank, etc.

data.enText: given as an honour, without the person having to have the usual qualifications

data.chText: 荣誉博士学位；荣誉学位

before.enText: of a position in an organization

data.chText: 司库的职位纯属义务性质。
data.enText: The post of treasurer is a purely honorary position.
treated like a member of group without actually belonging to it

data.chText: 她得到了男子般的待遇。
data.enText: She was treated as an honorary man.

data.text: Use an , not a , before honorary .

simple_means.memory_skill: honor 荣誉 + ary …的，有…性质的 → 荣誉的

tr: given as an honor without the normal duties

value.def: An honorary title or membership of a group is given to someone without their needing to have the necessary qualifications, usually because of their public achievements.

example.ex: He will be awarded the honorary degree in a ceremony at Newcastle University.
example.tran: 他将在纽卡斯尔大学的一个仪式上获授荣誉学位。

example.ex: ...an honorary member of the Golf Club.
example.tran: 高尔夫球俱乐部的名誉会员

value.tran: （称号、成员资格）荣誉的，名誉的

value.def: Honorary is used to describe an official job that is done without payment.

example.ex: ...the honorary secretary of the Cheshire Beekeepers' Association.
example.tran: 柴郡养蜂人协会名誉秘书
